<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Simple Blog</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }

    header {
      background-color: #333;
      color: white;
      padding: 20px 0;
      text-align: center;
    }

    nav a {
      color: white;
      text-decoration: none;
      margin: 0 15px;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 30px auto;
      padding: 0 20px;
    }

    .post {
      background-color: white;
      padding: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }

    .post h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
      color: #333;
    }

    .post p {
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    footer {
      background-color: #333;
      color: white;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 15px 0;
      position: fixed;
      bottom: 0;
      width: 100%;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <h1>My Simple Blog</h1>
    <nav>
      <a href="#">Home</a>
      <a href="#">About</a>
      <a href="#">Contact</a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="post">
      <h2>First Blog Post</h2>
      <p>Welcome to my blog! This is my first post. I'm excited to start sharing my thoughts and ideas with the world. Stay tuned for more updates!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="post">
      <h2>Another Day, Another Post</h2>
      <p>Today I learned how to create a blog layout using HTML and CSS. It's simple, clean, and works well on any device.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2025 My Simple Blog | All rights reserved.</p>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>
